From: Sean Christopherson <seanjc@google.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Sep 2025 17:33:02 -0700
Subject: KVM: x86: Drop pointless exports of kvm_arch_xxx() hooks
Git-commit: 6560468305da263c35ff51cde1dd74d6a228b286
Patch-mainline: v6.18-rc1
References: git-fixes

Drop the exporting of several kvm_arch_xxx() hooks that are only called
from arch-neutral code, i.e. that are only called from kvm.ko.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250919003303.1355064-5-seanjc@google.com
Signed-off-by: Sean Christopherson <seanjc@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Nikolay Borisov <nik.borisov@suse.com>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/x86.c |    3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/x86/kvm/x86.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/x86.c
@@ -13908,14 +13908,12 @@ void kvm_arch_register_noncoherent_dma(s
 	if (atomic_inc_return(&kvm->arch.noncoherent_dma_count) == 1)
 		kvm_noncoherent_dma_assignment_start_or_stop(kvm);
 }
-EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(kvm_arch_register_noncoherent_dma);
 
 void kvm_arch_unregister_noncoherent_dma(struct kvm *kvm)
 {
 	if (!atomic_dec_return(&kvm->arch.noncoherent_dma_count))
 		kvm_noncoherent_dma_assignment_start_or_stop(kvm);
 }
-EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(kvm_arch_unregister_noncoherent_dma);
 
 bool kvm_arch_has_noncoherent_dma(struct kvm *kvm)
 {
@@ -14012,7 +14010,6 @@ bool kvm_arch_no_poll(struct kvm_vcpu *v
 {
 	return (vcpu->arch.msr_kvm_poll_control & 1) == 0;
 }
-EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(kvm_arch_no_poll);
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_HAVE_KVM_ARCH_GMEM_PREPARE
 int kvm_arch_gmem_prepare(struct kvm *kvm, gfn_t gfn, kvm_pfn_t pfn, int max_order)
